rinary%20pathways.%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20developed%20and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreover,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Annotations%20for%20Uniprot%20that%20allows%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20genes%20and%20proteins%20given%20their%20related%20Molecular%20Process,%20Biological%20Function%20and%20Cellular%20Component%20location.%20Semantic%20Web?%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20built%20using%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies.%20The%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20an%20evolution%20of%20the%20current%20web%20that%20attempts%20to%20standardise%20the%20way%20data%20is%20published%20and%20shared%20on%20the%20web.%20The%20vision%20for%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20in%20principle%20very%20simple;%20if%20we%20standardise%20the%20way%20we%20publish%20data%20and%20describe%20the%20data,%20then%20it%20becomes%20easier%20to%20integrate%20these%20data%20and%20provides%20scope%20for%20more%20complex%20querying%20and%20analysis%20of%20the%20data.%20In%20the%20life%20sciences%20in%20particular,%20we%20have%20lots%20of%20data%20around,%20but%20integrating%20it%20is%20difficult%20because%20the%20raw%20data%20is%20either%20simply%20not%20available%20on%20the%20web%20or%20it%20comes%20in%20some%20bespoke%20format%20that%20needs%20translating%20into%20some%20other%20format%20before%20integration%20is%20possible.%20The%20problem%20isn%27t%20just%20formats,%20we%20also%20have%20problems%20with%20identifiers%20and%20names%20for%20the%20things%20we%20talk%20about%20in%20biology,%20such%20as%20genes,%20gene%20functions,%20diseases,%20anatomical%20parts,%20biomedical%20investigations,%20instruments%20etc..%20Luckily%20there%20is%20a%20whole%20community%20of%20biologists%20and%20computer%20scientist%20working%20to%20develop%20ontologies%20that%20will%20provide%20the%20community%20with%20a%20set%20of%20standard%20terminology%20to%20describe%20the%20data%20published%20on%20the%20web%20-%20many%20of%20you%20will%20already%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20Gene%20Ontology,%20but%20other%20ontologies%20now%20exist%20to%20cover%20many%20sub-domains%20of%20biology.%20The%20KUPKB%20makes%20extensive%20use%20of%20these%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20controlled%20and%20consistent%20annotation%20mechanism%20for%20the%20experimental%20data.%20Adopting%20these%20standards%20not%20only%20offers%20new%20ways%20to%20query%20and%20browse%20the%20data%20but%20it%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20integrate%20other%20datasets%20with%20the%20KUPKB%20data,%20providing%20everybody%20adheres%20to%20the%20same%20set%20of%20standards.%20%20Whilst%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20the%20first%20and%20probably%20not%20the%20last%20specialised%20kidney%20database%20that%20will%20emerge%20on%20the%20Web,%20it%20differs%20from%20previous%20efforts%20because%20of%20the%20way%20we%20represent%20and%20publish%20the%20data.%20All%20of%20the%20data%20is%20published%20in%20a%20single%20format%20called%20RDF.%20We%20have%20RDF%20versions%20of%20many%20biological%20databases%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20such%20as%20Entrez%20Gene,%20Uniprot,%20KEGG,%20HMDB,%20Homologene,%20String,%20Gene%20Ontology%20Annotations%20and%20HMDB.%20Various%20mapping%20work%20has%20been%20done%20to%20connected%20all%20of%20these%20databases%20using%20standard%20identifiers.%20Next,%20the%20experimental%20observations%20such%20as%20a%20gene%20list%20from%20a%20microarray%20experiment%20are%20also%20represented%20in%20RDF,%20and%20using%20the%20appropriate%20identifiers,%20linked%20to%20the%20appropriate%20reference%20databases.%20The%20experimental%20data%20is%20described%20using%20terms%20from%20standard%20ontologies%20that%20cover%20terms%20about%20renal%20cells,%20anatomy,%20animal%20models%20and%20diseases.%20This%20gives%20us%20a%20very%20rich%20connected%20knowledge%20base%20of%20facts%20about%20experimental%20observation%20in%20the%20kidney.%20The%20iKUP%20browser%20only%20exposes%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20rich%20data%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20we%20are%20currently%20working%20on%20more%20tools%20for%20this%20site%20that%20expose%20the%20rich%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB.%20The%20most%20powerful%20and%20flexible%20way%20to%20query%20this%20data%20is%20to%20query%20the%20RDF%20database%20directly,%20we%20can%20do%20this%20using%20an%20RDF%20query%20language%20called%20SPARQL.%20You%20can%20perfom%20sparql%20queries%20against%20the%20KUPKB%20using%20the%20query%20box%20in%20the%20SPARQL%20tab%20above;%20SPARQL%20is%20a%20low%20level%20query%20language%20and%20is%20going%20to%20be%20to%20everyones%20taste,%20however,%20we%20have%20provided%20some%20example%20queries%20to%20illustrate%20what%20is%20possible.%20Remember,%20if%20you%20submit%20your%20own%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB%20then%20it%20will%20instantly%20become%20integrated%20with%20all%20the%20other%20datasets%20already%20present.%20For%20help%20with%20SPARQL%20or%20any%20question%20please%20contact%20us%20via%20at%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20%20Want%20to%20submit%20your%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB?%20%20Then%20we%20are%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20assist%20you%20in%20doing%20so!!%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20simple%20spreadsheet%20template%20for%20users%20to%20submit%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20We%20aim%20to%20capture%20a%20minimal%20amount%20of%20information%20about%20the%20experiment%20and%20the%20observations%20made.%20Where%20possible%20we%20use%20a%20controlled%20vocabulary%20with%20terms%20from%20the%20KUP%20ontology%20that%20enables%20advanced%20querying%20capabilities%20in%20the%20iKUP%20browser.%20%20The%20template%20is%20distributed%20as%20an%20Microsft%20Excel%20spreadsheet%20and%20can%20be%20edited%20in%20either%20MS%20Excel%20or%20the%20open%20source%20tool%20OpenOffice.%20You%20can%20download%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20template%20from%20here.%20There%20are%20some%20instructions%20in%20the%20spreadsheet%20but%20you%20can%20also%20view%20an%20example%20from%20one%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20exepriements%20here.%20If%20you%20have%20any%20questions%20or%20would%20like%20assistanc%20in%20submitting%20your%20data%20please%20contact%20us%20via%20e-mail%20at%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20%20%20%20The%20primary%20contact%20for%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20via%20the%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org%20mailing%20list.%20Alternatively%20you%20can%20contact%20any%20of%20the%20group%20members%20from%20Manchester%20or%20Toulouse%20directly.%20Team%20KUPKB%20%20%20%20Dr%20Julie%20Klein%20%20%20Contact:%20julie(dot)klein(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Queen%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20first%20port%20of%20call%20for%20any%20questions%20relating%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20She%20will%20gladly%20help%20you%20get%20your%20data%20into%20the%20KUPKB%20in%20return%20for%20tea%20and%20biscuits.%20%20%20Bio:%20Julie%20Klein%20received%20her%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20in%202009%20from%20the%20University%20Paul%20Sabatier,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20This%20thesis%20aimed%20to%20unravel%20the%20role%20of%20the%20kinin%20B1%20receptor%20in%20the%20development%20of%20kidney%20inflammation%20and%20fibrosis%20and%20evaluate%20the%20therapeutic%20potential%20of%20a%20B1R%20antagonist%20on%20the%20progression%20of%20nephropathies.%20Since%202009,%20Julie%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20on%20the%20development%20of%20a%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Pathway%20Knowldge%20Base%20(KUPKB).%20%20%20%20%20%20Simon%20Jupp%20%20%20Contact:%20simon(dot)jupp(at)manchester(dot)ac(dot)uk%20%20%20Role:Programmer,%20architect%20and%20ontologist%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20%20%20Bio:%20Simon%20works%20in%20the%20Bio-Health%20Informatics%20Group%20(BHIG)%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester.%20He%20has%20degrees%20in%20both%20Biochemistry%20and%20Computer%20Science%20and%20now%20works%20primarily%20as%20a%20research%20bioinformatician.%20His%20interests%20are%20generally%20related%20to%20information%20management,%20but%20more%20specifically,%20using%20computers%20to%20improve%20the%20way%20we%20capture%20,%20manage%20and%20share%20knowledge%20about%20biology.%20Most%20of%20my%20work%20is%20now%20focused%20on%20the%20use%20of%20ontologies%20to%20capture%20knowledge%20in%20some%20computationally%20useful%20form.%20%20%20%2 0and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreover,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Annotations%20for%20Uniprot%20that%20allows%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20genes%20and%20proteins%20given%20their%20related%20Molecular%20Process,%20Biological%20Function%20and%20Cellular%20Component%20location.%20Semantic%20Web?%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20built%20using%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies.%20The%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20an%20evolution%20of%20the%20current%20web%20that%20attempts%20to%20standardise%20the%20way%20data%20is%20published%20and%20shared%20on%20the%20web.%20The%20vision%20for%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20in%20principle%20very%20simple;%20if%20we%20standardise%20the%20way%20we%20publish%20data%20and%20describe%20the%20data,%20then%20it%20becomes%20easier%20to%20integrate%20these%20data%20and%20provides%20scope%20for%20more%20complex%20querying%20and%20analysis%20of%20the%20data.%20In%20the%20life%20sciences%20in%20particular,%20we%20have%20lots%20of%20data%20around,%20but%20integrating%20it%20is%20difficult%20because%20the%20raw%20data%20is%20either%20simply%20not%20available%20on%20the%20web%20or%20it%20comes%20in%20some%20bespoke%20format%20that%20needs%20translating%20into%20some%20other%20format%20before%20integration%20is%20possible.%20The%20problem%20isn%27t%20just%20formats,%20we%20also%20have%20problems%20with%20identifiers%20and%20names%20for%20the%20things%20we%20talk%20about%20in%20biology,%20such%20as%20genes,%20gene%20functions,%20diseases,%20anatomical%20parts,%20biomedical%20investigations,%20instruments%20etc..%20Luckily%20there%20is%20a%20whole%20community%20of%20biologists%20and%20computer%20scientist%20working%20to%20develop%20ontologies%20that%20will%20provide%20the%20community%20with%20a%20set%20of%20standard%20terminology%20to%20describe%20the%20data%20published%20on%20the%20web%20-%20many%20of%20you%20will%20already%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20Gene%20Ontology,%20but%20other%20ontologies%20now%20exist%20to%20cover%20many%20sub-domains%20of%20biology.%20The%20KUPKB%20makes%20extensive%20use%20of%20these%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20controlled%20and%20consistent%20annotation%20mechanism%20for%20the%20experimental%20data.%20Adopting%20these%20standards%20not%20only%20offers%20new%20ways%20to%20query%20and%20browse%20the%20data%20but%20it%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20integrate%20other%20datasets%20with%20the%20KUPKB%20data,%20providing%20everybody%20adheres%20to%20the%20same%20set%20of%20standards.%20%20Whilst%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20the%20first%20and%20probably%20not%20the%20last%20specialised%20kidney%20database%20that%20will%20emerge%20on%20the%20Web,%20it%20differs%20from%20previous%20efforts%20because%20of%20the%20way%20we%20represent%20and%20publish%20the%20data.%20All%20of%20the%20data%20is%20published%20in%20a%20single%20format%20called%20RDF.%20We%20have%20RDF%20versions%20of%20many%20biological%20databases%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20such%20as%20Entrez%20Gene,%20Uniprot,%20KEGG,%20HMDB,%20Homologene,%20String,%20Gene%20Ontology%20Annotations%20and%20HMDB.%20Various%20mapping%20work%20has%20been%20done%20to%20connected%20all%20of%20these%20databases%20using%20standard%20identifiers.%20Next,%20the%20experimental%20observations%20such%20as%20a%20gene%20list%20from%20a%20microarray%20experiment%20are%20also%20represented%20in%20RDF,%20and%20using%20the%20appropriate%20identifiers,%20linked%20to%20the%20appropriate%20reference%20databases.%20The%20experimental%20data%20is%20described%20using%20terms%20from%20standard%20ontologies%20that%20cover%20terms%20about%20renal%20cells,%20anatomy,%20animal%20models%20and%20diseases.%20This%20gives%20us%20a%20very%20rich%20connected%20knowledge%20base%20of%20facts%20about%20experimental%20observation%20in%20the%20kidney.%20The%20iKUP%20browser%20only%20exposes%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20rich%20data%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20we%20are%20currently%20working%20on%20more%20tools%20for%20this%20site%20that%20expose%20the%20rich%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB.%20The%20most%20powerful%20and%20flexible%20way%20to%20query%20this%20data%20is%20to%20query%20the%20RDF%20database%20directly,%20we%20can%20do%20this%20using%20an%20RDF%20query%20language%20called%20SPARQL.%20You%20can%20perfom%20sparql%20queries%20against%20the%20KUPKB%20using%20the%20query%20box%20in%20the%20SPARQL%20tab%20above;%20SPARQL%20is%20a%20low%20level%20query%20language%20and%20is%20going%20to%20be%20to%20everyones%20taste,%20however,%20we%20have%20provided%20some%20example%20queries%20to%20illustrate%20what%20is%20possible.%20Remember,%20if%20you%20submit%20your%20own%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB%20then%20it%20will%20instantly%20become%20integrated%20with%20all%20the%20other%20datasets%20already%20present.%20For%20help%20with%20SPARQL%20or%20any%20question%20please%20contact%20us%20via%20at%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20%20Want%20to%20submit%20your%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB?%20%20Then%20we%20are%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20assist%20you%20in%20doing%20so!!%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20simple%20spreadsheet%20template%20for%20users%20to%20submit%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20We%20aim%20to%20capture%20a%20minimal%20amount%20of%20information%20about%20the%20experiment%20and%20the%20observations%20made.%20Where%20possible%20we%20use%20a%20controlled%20vocabulary%20with%20terms%20from%20the%20KUP%20ontology%20that%20enables%20advanced%20querying%20capabilities%20in%20the%20iKUP%20browser.%20%20The%20template%20is%20distributed%20as%20an%20Microsft%20Excel%20spreadsheet%20and%20can%20be%20edited%20in%20either%20MS%20Excel%20or%20the%20open%20source%20tool%20OpenOffice.%20You%20can%20download%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20template%20from%20here.%20There%20are%20some%20instructions%20in%20the%20spreadsheet%20but%20you%20can%20also%20view%20an%20example%20from%20one%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20exepriements%20here.%20If%20you%20have%20any%20questions%20or%20would%20like%20assistanc%20in%20submitting%20your%20data%20please%20contact%20us%20via%20e-mail%20at%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20%20%20%20The%20primary%20contact%20for%20the%20KUPKB%20i ontact:%20pmoulos(at)eie(dot)gr%20%20%20Role:New%20team%20member,%20trained%20in%20the%20dark%20arts%20of%20R%20and%20currently%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20KUPKB%20tools...%20%20%20Bio:%20Panagiotis%20Moulos%20holds%20a%20diploma%20in%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Physics%20and%20a%20MSc%20in%20Bioinformatics.%20In%202011,%20he%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Bioinformatics%20from%20the%20National%20Technical%20University%20of%20Athens,%20Greece%20(NTUA)%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20statistical%20algorithms%20and%20software%20development%20for%20the%20computational%20analysis%20and%20meta-analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20(DNA%20microarrays,%20Next%20Generation%20Sequencing).%20He%20is%20also%20interested%20in%20the%20application%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20techniques%20regarding%20the%20computational%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20the%20integration%20of%20lower%20level%20data%20representations%20(fundamental%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data)%20to%20higher%20level%20representations%20(over%20represented%20GO%20categories,%20mapping%20to%20metabolic%20pathways,%20building%20of%20transcriptional%20networks).%20He%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20in%20the%20RF-Lab%20at%20Inserm,%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra%20%20%20Contact:%20joost-peter(dot)schanstra(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Crash%20test%20dummy%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20Plays%20a%20mean%20slap%20bass%20guitar.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra,%20born%201967%20in%20Meppel,%20The%20Netherlands,%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20(1996)%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Groningen,%20The%20Netherlands.%20From%201996%20to%201999%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Inserm%20U388%20in%20Toulouse,%20France.%20In%201999%20he%20obtained%20a%20staff%20research%20position%20in%20the%20same%20laboratory.%20Since%202004%20he%20is%20group-leader%20of%2 0and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreover,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Annotations%20for%20Uniprot%20that%20allows%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20genes%20and%20proteins%20given%20their%20related%20Molecular%20Process,%20Biological%20Function%20and%20Cellular%20Component%20location.%20Semantic%20Web?%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20built%20using%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies.%20The%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20an%20evolution%20of%20the%20current%20web%20that%20attempts%20to%20standardise%20the%20way%20data%20is%20published%20and%20shared%20on%20the%20web.%20The%20vision%20for%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20in%20principle%20very%20simple;%20if%20we%20standardise%20the%20way%20we%20publish%20data%20and%20describe%20the%20data,%20then%20it%20becomes%20easier%20to%20integrate%20these%20data%20and%20provides%20scope%20for%20more%20complex%20querying%20and%20analysis%20of%20the%20data.%20In%20the%20life%20sciences%20in%20particular,%20we%20have%20lots%20of%20data%20around,%20but%20integrating%20it%20is%20difficult%20because%20the%20raw%20data%20is%20either%20simply%20not%20available%20on%20the%20web%20or%20it%20comes%20in%20some%20bespoke%20format%20that%20needs%20translating%20into%20some%20other%20format%20before%20integration%20is%20possible.%20The%20problem%20isn%27t%20just%20formats,%20we%20also%20have%20problems%20with%20identifiers%20and%20names%20for%20the%20things%20we%20talk%20about%20in%20biology,%20such%20as%20genes,%20gene%20functions,%20diseases,%20anatomical%20parts,%20biomedical%20investigations,%20instruments%20etc..%20Luckily%20there%20is%20a%20whole%20community%20of%20biologists%20and%20computer%20scientist%20working%20to%20develop%20ontologies%20that%20will%20provide%20the%20community%20with%20a%20set%20of%20standard%20terminology%20to%20describe%20the%20data%20published%20on%20the%20web%20-%20many%20of%20you%20will%20already%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20Gene%20Ontology,%20but%20other%20ontologies%20now%20exist%20to%20cover%20many%20sub-domains%20of%20biology.%20The%20KUPKB%20makes%20extensive%20use%20of%20these%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20controlled%20and%20consistent%20annotation%20mechanism%20for%20the%20experimental%20data.%20Adopting%20these%20standards%20not%20only%20offers%20new%20ways%20to%20query%20and%20browse%20the%20data%20but%20it%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20integrate%20other%20datasets%20with%20the%20KUPKB%20data,%20providing%20everybody%20adheres%20to%20the%20same%20set%20of%20standards.%20%20Whilst%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20the%20first%20and%20probably%20not%20the%20last%20specialised%20kidney%20database%20that%20will%20emerge%20on%20the%20Web,%20it%20differs%20from%20previous%20efforts%20because%20of%20the%20way%20we%20represent%20and%20publish%20the%20data.%20All%20of%20the%20data%20is%20published%20in%20a%20single%20format%20called%20RDF.%20We%20have%20RDF%20versions%20of%20many%20biological%20databases%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20such%20as%20Entrez%20Gene,%20Uniprot,%20KEGG,%20HMDB,%20Homologene,%20String,%20Gene%20Ontology%20Annotations%20and%20HMDB.%20Various%20mapping%20work%20has%20been%20done%20to%20connected%20all%20of%20these%20databases%20using%20standard%20identifiers.%20Next,%20the%20experimental%20observations%20such%20as%20a%20gene%20list%20from%20a%20microarray%20experiment%20are%20also%20represented%20in%20RDF,%20and%20using%20the%20appropriate%20identifiers,%20linked%20to%20the%20appropriate%20reference%20databases.%20The%20experimental%20data%20is%20described%20using%20terms%20from%20standard%20ontologies%20that%20cover%20terms%20about%20renal%20cells,%20anatomy,%20animal%20models%20and%20diseases.%20This%20gives%20us%20a%20very%20rich%20connected%20knowledge%20base%20of%20facts%20about%20experimental%20observation%20in%20the%20kidney.%20The%20iKUP%20browser%20only%20exposes%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20rich%20data%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20we%20are%20currently%20working%20on%20more%20tools%20for%20this%20site%20that%20expose%20the%20rich%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB.%20The%20most%20powerful%20and%20flexible%20way%20to%20query%20this%20data%20is%20to%20query%20the%20RDF%20database%20directly,%20we%20can%20do%20this%20using%20an%20RDF%20query%20language%20called%20SPARQL.%20You%20can%20perfom%20sparql%20queries%20against%20the%20KUPKB%20using%20the%20query%20box%20in%20the%20SPARQL%20tab%20above;%20SPARQL%20is%20a%20low%20level%20query%20language%20and%20is%20going%20to%20be%20to%20everyones%20taste,%20however,%20we%20have%20provided%20some%20example%20queries%20to%20illustrate%20what%20is%20possible.%20Remember,%20if%20you%20submit%20your%20own%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB%20then%20it%20will%20instantly%20become%20integrated%20with%20all%20the%20other%20datasets%20already%20present.%20For%20help%20with%20SPARQL%20or%20any%20question%20please%20contact%20us%20via%20at%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20%20Want%20to%20submit%20your%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB?%20%20Then%20we%20are%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20assist%20you%20in%20doing%20so!!%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20simple%20spreadsheet%20template%20for%20users%20to%20submit%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20We%20aim%20to%20capture%20a%20minimal%20amount%20of%20information%20about%20the%20experiment%20and%20the%20observations%20made.%20Where%20possible%20we%20use%20a%20controlled%20vocabulary%20with%20terms%20from%20the%20KUP%20ontology%20that%20enables%20advanced%20querying%20capabilities%20in%20the%20iKUP%20browser.%20%20The%20template%20is%20distributed%20as%20an%20Microsft%20Excel%20spreadsheet%20and%20can%20be%20edited%20in%20either%20MS%20Excel%20or%20the%20open%20source%20tool%20OpenOffice.%20You%20can%20download%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20template%20from%20here.%20There%20are%20some%20instructions%20in%20the%20spreadsheet%20but%20you%20can%20also%20view%20an%20example%20from%20one%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20exepriements%20here.%20If%20you%20have%20any%20questions%20or%20would%20like%20assistanc%20in%20submitting%20your%20data%20please%20contact%20us%20via%20e-mail%20at%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20%20%20%20The%20primary%20contact%20for%20the%20KUPKB%20i ontact:%20pmoulos(at)eie(dot)gr%20%20%20Role:New%20team%20member,%20trained%20in%20the%20dark%20arts%20of%20R%20and%20currently%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20KUPKB%20tools...%20%20%20Bio:%20Panagiotis%20Moulos%20holds%20a%20diploma%20in%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Physics%20and%20a%20MSc%20in%20Bioinformatics.%20In%202011,%20he%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Bioinformatics%20from%20the%20National%20Technical%20University%20of%20Athens,%20Greece%20(NTUA)%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20statistical%20algorithms%20and%20software%20development%20for%20the%20computational%20analysis%20and%20meta-analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20(DNA%20microarrays,%20Next%20Generation%20Sequencing).%20He%20is%20also%20interested%20in%20the%20application%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20techniques%20regarding%20the%20computational%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20the%20integration%20of%20lower%20level%20data%20representations%20(fundamental%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data)%20to%20higher%20level%20representations%20(over%20represented%20GO%20categories,%20mapping%20to%20metabolic%20pathways,%20building%20of%20transcriptional%20networks).%20He%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20in%20the%20RF-Lab%20at%20Inserm,%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra%20%20%20Contact:%20joost-peter(dot)schanstra(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Crash%20test%20dummy%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20Plays%20a%20mean%20slap%20bass%20guitar.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra,%20born%201967%20in%20Meppel,%20The%20Netherlands,%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20(1996)%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Groningen,%20The%20Netherlands.%20From%201996%20to%201999%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Inserm%20U388%20in%20Toulouse,%20France.%20In%201999%20he%20obtained%20a%20staff%20research%20position%20in%20the%20same%20laboratory.%20Since%202004%20he%20is%20group-leader%20of%2 0and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreover,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Anno ontact:%20pmoulos(at)eie(dot)gr%20%20%20Role:New%20team%20member,%20trained%20in%20the%20dark%20arts%20of%20R%20and%20currently%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20KUPKB%20tools...%20%20%20Bio:%20Panagiotis%20Moulos%20holds%20a%20diploma%20in%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Physics%20and%20a%20MSc%20in%20Bioinformatics.%20In%202011,%20he%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Bioinformatics%20from%20the%20National%20Technical%20University%20of%20Athens,%20Greece%20(NTUA)%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20statistical%20algorithms%20and%20software%20development%20for%20the%20computational%20analysis%20and%20meta-analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20(DNA%20microarrays,%20Next%20Generation%20Sequencing).%20He%20is%20also%20interested%20in%20the%20application%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20techniques%20regarding%20the%20computational%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20the%20integration%20of%20lower%20level%20data%20representations%20(fundamental%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data)%20to%20higher%20level%20representations%20(over%20represented%20GO%20categories,%20mapping%20to%20metabolic%20pathways,%20building%20of%20transcriptional%20networks).%20He%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20in%20the%20RF-Lab%20at%20Inserm,%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra%20%20%20Contact:%20joost-peter(dot)schanstra(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Crash%20test%20dummy%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20Plays%20a%20mean%20slap%20bass%20guitar.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra,%20born%201967%20in%20Meppel,%20The%20Netherlands,%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20(1996)%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Groningen,%20The%20Netherlands.%20From%201996%20to%201999%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Inserm%20U388%20in%20Toulouse,%20France.%20In%201999%20he%20obtained%20a%20staff%20research%20position%20in%20the%20same%20laboratory.%20Since%202004%20he%20is%20group-leader%20of%2 0and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreover,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Anno ontact:%20pmoulos(at)eie(dot)gr%20%20%20Role:New%20team%20member,%20trained%20in%20the%20dark%20arts%20of%20R%20and%20currently%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20KUPKB%20tools...%20%20%20Bio:%20Panagiotis%20Moulos%20holds%20a%20diploma%20in%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Physics%20and%20a%20MSc%20in%20Bioinformatics.%20In%202011,%20he%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Bioinformatics%20from%20the%20National%20Technical%20University%20of%20Athens,%20Greece%20(NTUA)%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20statistical%20algorithms%20and%20software%20development%20for%20the%20computational%20analysis%20and%20meta-analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20(DNA%20microarrays,%20Next%20Generation%20Sequencing).%20He%20is%20also%20interested%20in%20the%20application%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20techniques%20regarding%20the%20computational%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20the%20integration%20of%20lower%20level%20data%20representations%20(fundamental%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data)%20to%20higher%20level%20representations%20(over%20represented%20GO%20categories,%20mapping%20to%20metabolic%20pathways,%20building%20of%20transcriptional%20networks).%20He%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20in%20the%20RF-Lab%20at%20Inserm,%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra%20%20%20Contact:%20joost-peter(dot)schanstra(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Crash%20test%20dummy%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20Plays%20a%20mean%20slap%20bass%20guitar.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra,%20born%201967%20in%20Meppel,%20The%20Netherlands,%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20(1996)%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Groningen,%20The%20Netherlands.%20From%201996%20to%201999%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Inserm%20U388%20in%20Toulouse,%20France.%20In%201999%20he%20obtained%20a%20staff%20research%20position%20in%20the%20same%20laboratory.%20Since%202004%20he%20is%20group-leader%20of%2 20for%20diseases%20affecting%20the%20kidney%20and%20urinary%20pathways.%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20developed%20and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Steven -domains%20of%20biology.%20The%20KUPKB%20makes%20extensive%20use%20of%20these%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20controlled%20and%20consistent%20annotation%20mechanism%20for%20the%20experimental%20data.%20Adopting%20these%20standards%20not%20only%20offers%20new%20ways%20to%20query%20and%20browse%20the%20data%20but%20it%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20integrate%20other%20datasets%20with%20the%20KUPKB%20data,%20providing%20everybody%20adheres%20to%20the%20same%20set%20of%20standards.%20%20Whilst%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20the%20first%20and%20probably%20not%20the%20last%20specialised%20kidney%20database%20that%20will%20emerge%20on%20the%20Web,%20it%20differs%20from%20previous%20efforts%20because%20of%20the%20way%20we%20represent%20and%20publish%20the%20data.%20All%20of%20the%20data%20is%20published%20in%20a%20single%20format%20called%20RDF.%20We%20have%20RDF%20versions%20of%20many%20biological%20databases%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20such%20as%20Entrez%20Gene,%20Uniprot,%20KEGG,%20HMDB,%20Homologene,%20String,%20Gene%20Ontology%20Annotations%20and%20HMDB.%20Various%20mapping%20work%20has%20been%20done%20to%20connected%20all%20of%20these%20databases%20using%20standard%20identifiers.%20Next,%20the%20experimental%20observations%20such%20as%20a%20gene%20list%20from%20a%20microarray%20experiment%20are%20also%20represented%20in%20RDF,%20and%20using%20the%20appropriate%20identifiers,%20linked%20to%20the%20appropriate%20reference%20databases.%20The%20experimental%20data%20is%20described%20using%20terms%20from%20standard%20ontologies%20that%20cover%20terms%20about%20renal%20cells,%20anatomy,%20animal%20models%20and%20diseases.%20This%20gives%20us%20a%20very%20rich%20connected%20knowledge%20base%20of%20facts%20about%20experimental%20observation%20in%20the%20kidney.%20The%20iKUP%20browser%20only%20exposes%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20rich%20data%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20we%20are%20currently%20working%20on%20more%20tools%20for%20this%20site%20that%20expose%20t %20some%20computationally%20useful%20form.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Panagiotis%20(Panos)%20Moulos%20%20%20Contact:%20pmoulos(at)eie(dot)gr%20%20%20Role:New%20team%20member,%20trained%20in%20the%20dark%20arts%20of%20R%20and%20currently%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20KUPKB%20tools...%20%20%20Bio:%20Panagiotis%20Moulos%20holds%20a%20diploma%20in%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Physics%20and%20a%20MSc%20in%20Bioinformatics.%20In%202011,%20he%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Bioinformatics%20from%20the%20National%20Technical%20University%20of%20Athens,%20Greece%20(NTUA)%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20statistical%20algorithms%20and%20software%20development%20for%20the%20computational%20analysis%20and%20meta-analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20(DNA%20microarrays,%20Next%20Generation%20Sequencing).%20He%20is%20also%20interested%20in%20the%20application%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20techniques%20regarding%20the%20computational%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20the%20integration%20of%20lower%20level%20data%20representations%20(fundamental%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data)%20to%20higher%20level%20representations%20(over%20represented%20GO%20categories,%20mapping%20to%20metabolic%20pathways,%20building%20of%20transcriptional%20networks).%20He%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20in%20the%20RF-Lab%20at%20Inserm,%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra%20%20%20Contact:%20joost-peter(dot)schanstra(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Crash%20test%20dummy%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20Plays%20a%20mean%20slap%20bass%20guitar.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra,%20born%201967%20in%20Meppel,%20The%20Netherlands,%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20(1996)%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Groningen,%20The%20Netherlands.%20From%201996%20to%201999%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Inserm%20U388%20in%20Toulouse,%20France.%20In%201999%20he%20obtained%20a%20staff%20research%20position%20in%20the%20same%20laboratory.%20Since%202004%20he%20is%20group-leader%20of%20the%20RF-lab%20with%20Jean-Loup%20Bascands%20at%20Inserm%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20%20%20Contact:%20robert(dot)stevens(at)manchester(dot)ac(dot)uk%20%20%20Role:%20High%20flying%20academic%20and%20ontology%20guru.%20Ability%20to%20speak%20at%20length%20and%20with%20utter%20authority%20about%20any%20subject.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20is%20a%20reader%20in%20BioHealth%20Informatics%20in%20the%20Bio%20and%20Health%20Informatics%20Group%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester.%20His%20main%20areas%20of%20research%20interest%20within%20these%20domains%20are%20the%20development%20and%20use%20of%20ontologies%20to%20describe%20biology%20to%20make%20knowledge%20about%20molecular%20biology%20computationally%20useful.%20He%20is%20particularly%20interested%20in%20the%20communal%20building%20of%20ontologies%20--%20enabling%20domain%20experts%20to%20use%20the%20power%20of%20formal,%20expressive%20languages,%20such%20as%20the%20Web%20Ontology%20Language%20(OWL).%20This%20interest%20extends%20back%20from%20this%20formal%20part%20of%20the%20process%20of%20ontology%20building%20back%20to%20the%20initial%20stages%20of%20the%20process%20where%20he%20has%20an%20interest%20in%20rapid%20development%20of%20vocabularies%20and%20ontologies%20from%20text.%20He%20also%20has%20an%20interest%20in%20e-Science%20with%20the%20use%20of%20the%20taverna%20workbench%20from%20the%20myGrid%20project%20to%20industrialise%20the%20bioinformatics%20analysis%20of%20data.%20Ontologies%20and%20semantic%20description%20of%20content%20through%20ontologies%20also%20plays%20a%20part%20in%20this%20e-Science%20research.%20%20%20%20Thank%20you!%20We%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20a%20number%20of%20individuals%20from%20the%20EuroKUP%20community%20for%20contributing%20to%20the%20KUP-ontology.%20EuroKUP%20(European%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Proteomics),%20yes%20KUP%20stands%20for%20something%20somewhat%20different%20in%20the%20KUPKB,%20is%20an%20FP7%20COST-initiative%20focusing%20on%20facilitating%20translational%20proteomic%20research%20in%20kidney%20diseases%20by%20bringing%20together%20and%20promoting%20interactions%20between%20basic%20scientists%20and%20clinicians%20working%20in%20the%20broader%20areas%20of%20kidney%20and%20urine%20proteomics.%20First%20of%20all%20we%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20all%20EuroKUP%20members%20that%20contributed%20to%20the%20KUP-ontology%20day%20that%20was%20held%20on%20November%202,%202009%20in%20Manchester.%20We%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20the%20following%20EuroKUP%20members%20more%20specifically%20for%20their%20continued%20help%20on%20the%20ontology:%20Antonia%20Vlahou,%20Jorgen%20Frokaier,%20Aristidis%20Charonis,%20Alberto%20Ortiz%20and%20Harry%20Holthofer.%20%20%20We%20would%20also%20acknowledge%20the%20help%20of%20the%20entire%20RF-lab%20for%20their%20continuous%20support%20and%20their%20constructive%20comments.%20Sorry%20for%20our%20repeated%20harassments.%20Thank%20you%20in%20advance%20for%20being%20our%20first%20testers.%20%20%20The%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Pathway%20Knowledge%20Base%20is%20designed%20for%20researchers,%20physicians%20and%20students%20of%20these%20professions%20in%20the%20field.%20%20Content%20is%20not%20asserted%20complete%20or%20error%20free.%20As%20with%20any%20textbook,%20coverage%20can%20never%20be%20complete.%20Information%20may%20also%20become%20out%20of%20date.%20We%20encourage%20suggestions%20for%20additional%20content%20or%20notification%20of%20possible%20errors.%20We%20do%20not%20enter%20into%20correspondence%20on%20any%20individual%27s%20case%20history%20or%20clinical%20condition%20and%20we%20do%20not%20offer%20personalised%20medical%20advice%20on%20any%20KUP%20related%20disease.%20%20Answers%20to%20frequently%20asked%20questions%20about%20database%20content,%20editorial%20policy,%20funding%20etc%20are%20found%20here.%20I%20want%20to%20add%20my%20data%20or%20data%20that%20I%20found%20in%20the%20literature%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20What%20should%20I%20do?%20See%20the%20%E2%80%9CSubmit%20data%E2%80%9D%20section.%20If%20you%20need%20more%20information%20or%20help%20please%20send%20a%20mail%20to%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20I%20want%20to%20report%20a%20bug.%20What%20should%20I%20do?%20Please%20send%20a%20mail%20to%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org,%20and%20we%20will%20try%20to%20answer%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20I%20want%20to%20cite%20the%20KUPKB%20since%20I%20used%20it%20in%20my%20research.%20Is%20there%20any%20publication%20related%20to%20the%20KUPKB?%20We%20are%20currently%20preparing%20a%20manuscript%20for%20the%20kupkb%20application.%20In%20the%20meantime%20you%20can%20cite%20the%20following%20paper%20which%20describes%20the%20ontology%20development%20and%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies%20used%20to%20build%20the%20KUPKB:%20%20Simon%20Jupp,%20Julie%20Klein,%20Joost%20Schanstra%20and%20Robert%20Stevens.%20Developing%20a%20kidney%20and%20urinary%20pathway%20knowledge%20base.%20Journal%20of%20Biomedical%20Semantics%202011,%202(Suppl%202):S7.%20Is%20the%20KUPKB%20manually%20curated?%20All%20the%20data%20contained%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20have%20been%20manually%20extracted%20from%20figures%20and%20supplementary%20data.%20However,%20no%20further%20%E2%80%9Csubjective%E2%80%9D%20selection%20of%20the%20data%20has%20been%20performed%20by%20the%20KUPKB%20team%20before%20integration.%20We%20decided%20to%20let%20the%20user%20judge%20on%20relevancy%20of%20the%20data%20based%20on%20their%20own%20criteria,%20which%20may%20strongly%20differ%20from%20one%20to%20another,%20especially%20by:%201)%20giving%20some%20details%20about%20the%20analysis%20(extracted%20from%20the%20abstract%20or%20the%20material%20and%20method%20section),%202)%20giving%20the%20link%20to%20the%20full%20publication%20and%203)%20giving,%20when%20possible,%20the%20p-values%20and%20FDR%20values.%20How%20are%20the%20data%20analysed?%20In%20most%20cases,%20da ound%20adjustment%20to%20eliminate%20non-specific%20and%20cross%20hybridization%20effects,%20followed%20by%20quantile%20normalization%20and%20median%20polish%20summarization%20to%20extract%20transcript%20expression%20values.%20Statistical%20selection%20of%20differentially%20genes%20was%20based%20on%20a%20p-value%3C0,05%20and%20a%20FDR%20Benjamini-Hochberg%20q%3C0,05.%20%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20I%20find%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20that%20are%20present%20in%20a%20publication?%20The%20content%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20asserted%20complete%20or%20error%20free.%20We%20strongly%20encourage%20users%20to%20submit%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB%20team%20so%20they%20can%20be%20integrated%20in%20newer%20versions.%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20The%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Pathway%20Knowledge%20Base%20has%20been%20developed%20in%20collaboration%20between%20the%20Renal%20Fibrosis%20Laboratory%20at%20INSERM,%20France%20and%20the%20Bio-health%20Informatics%20Group%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester,%20UK.%20This%20work%20has%20been%20funded%20by%20e-LICO%20project,%20an%20EU-FP7%20Collaborative%20Project%20(2009-2012)%20Theme%20ICT-4.4:%20Intelligent%20Content%20and%20Semantics.%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20var%20pkBaseURL%20=%20((%22https:%22%20==%20document.location.protocol)%20?%20%22https://194.57.225.115/piwik/%22%20:%20%22http://194.57.225.115/piwik/%22);document.write(unescape(%22%3Cscript%20src=%27%22%20+%20pkBaseURL%20+%20%22piwik.js%27%20type=%27text/javascript%27%3E%3C/script%3E%22));try%20{var%20piwikTracker%20=%20Piwik.getTracker(pkBaseURL%20+%20%22piwik.php%22,%201);piwikTracker.trackPageView();piwikTracker.enableLinkTracking();}%20catch(%20err%20)%20{}%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src=%22http://194.57. r,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Annotations%20for%20Uniprot%20that%20allows%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20genes%20and%20proteins%20given%20their%20related%20Molecular%20Process,%20Biological%20Function%20and%20Cellular%20Component%20location.%20Semantic%20Web?%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20built%20using%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies.%20The%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20an%20evolution%20of%20the%20current%20web%20that%20attempts%20to%20standardise%20the%20way%20data%20is%20published%20and%20shared%20on%20the%20web.%20The%20vision%20for%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20in%20principle%20very%20simple;%20if%20we%20standardise%20the%20way%20we%20publish%20data%20and%20describe%20the%20data,%20then%20it%20becomes%20easier%20to%20integrate%20these%20data%20and%20provides%20scope%20for%20more%20complex%20querying%20and%20analysis%20of%20the%20data.%20In%20the%20life%20sciences%20in%20particular,%20we%20have%20lots%20of%20data%20around,%20but%20integrating%20it%20is%20difficult%20because%20the%20raw%20data%20is%20either%20simply%20not%20available%20on%20the%20web%20or%20it%20comes%20in%20some%20bespoke%20format%20that%20needs%20translating%20into%20some%20other%20format%20before%20integration%20is%20possible.%20The%20problem%20isn%27t%20just%20formats,%20we%20also%20have%20problems%20with%20identifiers%20and%20names%20for%20the%20things%20we%20talk%20about%20in%20biology,%20such%20as%20genes,%20gene%20functions,%20diseases,%20anatomical%20parts,%20biomedical%20investigations,%20instruments%20etc..%20Luckily%20there%20is%20a%20whole%20community%20of%20biologists%20and%20computer%20scientist%20working%20to%20develop%20ontologies%20that%20will%20provide%20the%20community%20with%20a%20set%20of%20standard%20terminology%20to%20describe%20the%20data%20published%20on%20the%20web%20-%20many%20of%20you%20will%20already%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20Gene%20Ontology,%20but%20other%20ontologies%20now%20exist%20to%20cover%20many%20sub-domains%20of%20biology.%20The%20KUPKB%20makes%20ex %20%20The%20primary%20contact%20for%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20via%20the%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org%20mailing%20list.%20Alternatively%20you%20can%20contact%20any%20of%20the%20group%20members%20from%20Manchester%20or%20Toulouse%20directly.%20Team%20KUPKB%20%20%20%20Dr%20Julie%20Klein%20%20%20Contact:%20julie(dot)klein(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Queen%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20first%20port%20of%20call%20for%20any%20questions%20relating%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20She%20will%20gladly%20help%20you%20get%20your%20data%20into%20the%20KUPKB%20in%20return%20for%20tea%20and%20biscuits.%20%20%20Bio:%20Julie%20Klein%20received%20her%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20in%202009%20from%20the%20University%20Paul%20Sabatier,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20This%20thesis%20aimed%20to%20unravel%20the%20role%20of%20the%20kinin%20B1%20receptor%20in%20the%20development%20of%20kidney%20inflammation%20and%20fibrosis%20and%20evaluate%20the%20therapeutic%20potential%20of%20a%20B1R%20antagonist%20on%20the%20progression%20of%20nephropathies.%20Since%202009,%20Julie%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20on%20the%20development%20of%20a%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Pathway%20Knowldge%20Base%20(KUPKB).%20%20%20%20%20%20Simon%20Jupp%20%20%20Contact:%20simon(dot)jupp(at)manchester(dot)ac(dot)uk%20%20%20Role:Programmer,%20architect%20and%20ontologist%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20%20%20Bio:%20Simon%20works%20in%20the%20Bio-Health%20Informatics%20Group%20(BHIG)%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester.%20He%20has%20degrees%20in%20both%20Biochemistry%20and%20Computer%20Science%20and%20now%20works%20primarily%20as%20a%20research%20bioinformatician.%20His%20interests%20are%20generally%20related%20to%20information%20management,%20but%20more%20specifically,%20using%20computers%20to%20improve%20the%20way%20we%20capture%20,%20manage%20and%20share%20knowledge%20about%20biology.%20Most%20of%20my%20work%20is%20now%20focused%20on%20the%20use%20of%20ontologies%20to%20capture%20knowledge%20in%20some%20computationally%20useful%20form.%20%20%20 0urinary%20pathways.%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20developed%20and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreove atory.%20Since%202004%20he%20is%20group-leader%20of%20the%20RF-lab%20with%20Jean-Loup%20Bascands%20at%20Inserm%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20%20%20Contact:%20robert(dot)stevens(at)manchester(dot)ac(dot)uk%20%20%20Role:%20High%20flying%20academic%20and%20ontology%20guru.%20Ability%20to%20speak%20at%20length%20and%20with%20utter%20authority%20about%20any%20subject.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20is%20a%20reader%20in%20BioHealth%20Informatics%20in%20the%20Bio%20and%20Health%20Informatics%20Group%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester.%20His%20main%20areas%20of%20research%20interest%20within%20these%20domains%20are%20the%20development%20and%20use%20of%20ontologies%20to%20describe%20biology%20to%20make%20knowledge%20about%20molecular%20biology%20computationally%20useful.%20He%20is%20particularly%20interested%20in%20the%20communal%20building%20of%20ontologies%20--%20enabling%20domain%20experts%20to%20use%20the%20power%20of%20formal,%20expressive%20languages,%20such%20as%20the%20Web%20Ontology%20Language%20(OWL).%20This%20interest%20extends%20back%20from%20this%20formal%20part%20of%20the%20process%20of%20ontology%20building%20back%20to%20the%20initial%20stages%20of%20the%20process%20where%20he%20has%20an%20interest%20in%20rapid%20development%20of%20vocabularies%20and%20ontologies%20from%20text.%20He%20also%20has%20an%20interest%20in%20e-Science%20with%20the%20use%20of%20the%20taverna%20workbench%20from%20the%20myGrid%20project%20to%20industrialise%20the%20bioinformatics%20analysis%20of%20data.%20Ontologies%20and%20semantic%20description%20of%20content%20through%20ontologies%20also%20plays%20a%20part%20in%20this%20e-Science%20research.%20%20%20%20Thank%20you!%20We%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20a%20number%20of%20individuals%20from%20the%20EuroKUP%20community%20for%20contributing%20to%20the%20KUP-ontology.%20EuroKUP%20(European%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Proteomics),%20yes%20KUP%20stands%20for%20something%20somewhat%20different%20in%20the%20KUPKB,%20is%20an%20FP7%20COST-initiative%20focusing%20on%20facilitating%20translational%20proteomic%20research%20in%20kidney%20diseases%20by%20bringing%20together%20and%20promoting%20interactions%20between%20basic%20scientists%20and%20clinicians%20working%20in%20the%20broader%20areas%20of%20kidney%20and%20urine%20proteomics.%20First%20of%20all%20we%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20all%20EuroKUP%20members%20that%20contributed%20to%20the%20KUP-ontology%20day%20that%20was%20held%20on%20November%202,%202009%20in%20Manchester.%20We%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20the%20following%20EuroKUP%20members%20more%20specifically%20for%20their%20continued%20help%20on%20the%20ontology:%20Antonia%20Vlahou,%20Jorgen%20Frokaier,%20Aristidis%20Charonis,%20Alberto%20Ortiz%20and%20Harry%20Holthofer.%20%20%20We%20would%20also%20acknowledge%20the%20help%20of%20the%20entire%20RF-lab%20for%20their%20continuous%20support%20and%20their%20constructive%20comments.%20Sorry%20for%20our%20repeated%20harassments.%20Thank%20you%20in%20advance%20for%20being%20our%20first%20testers.%20%20%20The%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Pathway%20Knowledge%20Base%20is%20designed%20for%20researchers,%20physicians%20and%20students%20of%20these%20professions%20in%20the%20field.%20%20Content%20is%20not%20asserted%20complete%20or%20error%20free.%20As%20with%20any%20textbook,%20coverage%20can%20never%20be%20complete.%20Information%20may%20also%20become%20out%20of%20date.%20We%20encourage%20suggestions%20for%20additional%20content%20or%20notification%20of%20possible%20errors.%20We%20do%20not%20enter%20into%20correspondence%20on%20any%20individual%27s%20case%20history%20or%20clinical%20condition%20and%20we%20do%20not%20offer%20personalised%20medical%20advice%20on%20any%20KUP%20related%20disease.%20%20Answers%20to%20frequently%20asked%20questions%20about%20database%20content,%20editorial%20policy,%20funding%20etc%20are%20found%20here.%20I%20want%20to%20add%20my%20data%20or%20data%20that%20I%20found%20in%20the%20literature%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20What%20should%20I%20do?%20See%20the%20%E2%80%9CSubmit%20data%E2%80%9D%20section.%20If%20you%20need%20more%20information%20or%20help%20please%20send%20a%20mail%20to%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org.%20I%20want%20to%20report%20a%20bug.%20What%20should%20I%20do?%20Please%20send%20a%20mail%20to%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org,%20and%20we%20will%20try%20to%20answer%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20I%20want%20to%20cite%20the%20KUPKB%20since%20I%20used%20it%20in%20my%20research.%20Is%20there%20any%20publication%20related%20to%20the%20KUPKB?%20We%20are%20currently%20preparing%20a%20manuscript%20for%20the%20kupkb%20application.%20In%20the%20meantime%20you%20can%20cite%20the%20following%20paper%20which%20describes%20the%20ontology%20development%20and%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies%20used%20to%20build%20the%20KUPKB:%20%20Simon%20Jupp,%20Julie%20Klein,%20Joost%20Schanstra%20and%20Robert%20Stevens.%20Developing%20a%20kidney%20and%20urinary%20pathway%20knowledge%20base.%20Journal%20of%20Biomedical%20Semantics%202011,%202(Suppl%202):S7.%20Is%20the%20KUPKB%20manually%20curated?%20All%20the%20data%20contained%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20have%20been%20manually%20extracted%20from%20figures%20and%20supplementary%20data.%20However,%20no%20further%20%E2%80%9Csubjective%E2%80%9D%20selection%20of%20the%20data%20has%20been%20performed%20by%20the%20KUPKB%20team%20before%20integration.%20We%20decided%20to%20let%20the%20user%20judge%20on%20relevancy%20of%20the%20data%20based%20on%20their%20own%20criteria,%20which%20may%20strongly%20differ%20from%20one%20to%20another,%20especially%20by:%201)%20giving%20some%20details%20about%20the%20analysis%20(extracted%20from%20the%20abstract%20or%20the%20material%20and%20method%20section),%202)%20giving%20the%20link%20to%20the%20full%20publication%20and%203)%20giving,%20when%20possible,%20the%20p-values%20and%20FDR%20values.%20How%20are%20the%20data%20analysed?%20In%20most%20cases,%20data%20are%20extracted%20from%20figures%20and%20supplementary%20data.%20In%20this%20case,%20the%20data%20have%20been%20integrated%20exactly%20as%20they%20were%20published,%20without%20further%20analysis.%20Details%20on%20the%20analysis%20done%20by%20the%20authors%20analysis%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20original%20publication%20as%20we%20link%20each%20experiment%20to%20its%20respective%20Pubmed%20id%20(PMID).%20However,%20when%20available,%20some%20of%20the%20raw%20datasets%20have%20been%20downloaded%20from%20GEO.%20In%20this%20case,%20the%20data%20has%20been%20analysed%20by%20the%20KUPKB%20team%20one%20of%20the%20following%20two%20approaches%20(specified%20in%20the%20experiment%20description):%20%20Data%20were%20analyzed%20using%20R%20and%20Bioconductor%20as%20follows:%20raw%20Affymetrix%20CEL%20files%20were%20downloaded%20from%20GEO%20and%20subjected%20to%20GCRMA%20background%20adjustment%20to%20eliminate%20non-specific%20and%20cross%20hybridization%20effects,%20followed%20by%20quantile%20normalization%20and%20median%20polish%20summarization%20to%20extract%20transcript%20expression%20values.%20Each%20transcript%20was%20then%20categorized%20as%20present%20(P)%20if%20its%20MAS5%20call%20was%20%E2%80%9CPresent%E2%80%9D%20in%20at%20least%2050%%20of%20the%20experimental%20samples%20or%20absent%20(A)%20otherwise.%20All%20transcripts%20were%20averaged%20across%20each%20experimental%20class%20and%20in%20addition,%20those%20characterized%20as%20present%20were%20further%20categorized%20for%20each%20experimental%20class%20as%20%E2%80%9CWeak%E2%80%9D,%20%E2%80%9CMedium%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CStrong%E2%80%9D%20if%20their%20log2%20expression%20value%20fell%20below%20the%201st,%20between%20the%202nd%20and%203rd%20or%20above%20the%203rd%20quartiles%20of%20the%20averaged%20transcript%20distribution%20respectively.%20Data%20were%20analyzed%20using%20GeneArmada%20as%20follows:%20raw%20Affymetrix%20CEL%20files%20were%20downloaded%20from%20GEO%20and%20subjected%20to%20GCRMA%20background%20adjustment%20to%20eliminate%20non-specific%20and%20cross%20hybridization%20effects,%20followed%20by%20quantile%20normalization%20and%20median%20polish%20summarization%20to%20extract%20transcript%20expression%20values.%20Statistical%20selection%20of%20differentially%20genes%20was%20based%20on%20a%20p-value%3C0,05%20and%20a%20FDR%20Benjamini-Hochberg%20q%3C0,05.%20%20Why%20can%E2%80%99t%20I%20find%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20that%20are%20present%20in%20a%20publication?%20The%20content%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20asserted%20complete%20or%20error%20free.%20We%20strongly%20encourage%20users%20to%20submit%20data%20to%20the%20KUPKB%20team%20so%20they%20can%20be%20integrated%20in%20newer%20versions.%20%20%20 0urinary%20pathways.%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20developed%20and%20maintained%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester%20(UK)%20and%20Inserm%20Toulouse%20(France).%20Experimental%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20The%20KUPKB%20contains%20experimental%20data%20(mRNA,%20proteins%20and%20miRNA)%20coming%20from%20published%20articles%20in%20Pubmed,%20all%20related%20to%20kidney%20physiology%20and%20pathology.%20The%20data%20have%20been%20extracted%20manually%20from%20the%20figures%20or%20from%20the%20supplementary%20data%20when%20possible.%20Some%20microarray%20raw%20datasets%20have%20also%20been%20downloaded%20from%20the%20Gene%20Expression%20Omnibus%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20open-source%20software%20GeneArmada.%20Creating%20links%20between%20genes,%20proteins%20and%20pathways%20The%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20external%20resources%20such%20as%20NCBI%20gene,%20UniProt,%20Homologene%20and%20KEGG.%20This%20additional%20knowledge%20layer%20provides%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20link%20genes%20and%20proteins%20when%20searching%20for%20a%20given%20gene%20symbol,%20but%20also%20to%20link%20the%20orthologs%20from%20different%20species.%20Moreover,%20proteins%20are%20linked%20to%20KEGG%20pathways%20when%20possible,%20making%20the%20KUPKB%20able%20to%20be%20queried%20for%20specific%20biological%20pathways.%20Using%20ontologies%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20the%20data%20The%20KUPKB%20uses%20bio-medical%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20common%20vocabulary%20for%20describing%20kidney%20anatomy,%20cells%20or%20diseases.%20Ontologies%20capture%20the%20relationships%20between%20terms%20and%20express%20these%20relationships%20in%20a%20language%20that%20can%20be%20interpreted%20by%20a%20computer.%20We%20have%20developed%20a%20specialised%20KUP%20Ontology%20to%20annotate%20the%20experiments,%20which%20allows%20us%20to%20perform%20flexible%20queries%20and%20inference%20over%20the%20data%20(See%20a%20short%20article%20by%20Dr%20Robert%20Stevens%20on%20ontology%20in%20Biology%20here).%20Moreover,%20the%20KUPKB%20has%20integrated%20the%20GO%20Annotations%20for%20Uniprot%20that%20allows%20to%20annotate%20and%20query%20genes%20and%20proteins%20given%20their%20related%20Molecular%20Process,%20Biological%20Function%20and%20Cellular%20Component%20location.%20Semantic%20Web?%20The%20KUPKB%20is%20built%20using%20Semantic%20Web%20technologies.%20The%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20an%20evolution%20of%20the%20current%20web%20that%20attempts%20to%20standardise%20the%20way%20data%20is%20published%20and%20shared%20on%20the%20web.%20The%20vision%20for%20the%20Semantic%20Web%20is%20in%20principle%20very%20simple;%20if%20we%20standardise%20the%20way%20we%20publish%20data%20and%20describe%20the%20data,%20then%20it%20becomes%20easier%20to%20integrate%20these%20data%20and%20provides%20scope%20for%20more%20complex%20querying%20and%20analysis%20of%20the%20data.%20In%20the%20life%20sciences%20in%20particular,%20we%20have%20lots%20of%20data%20around,%20but%20integrating%20it%20is%20difficult%20because%20the%20raw%20data%20is%20either%20simply%20not%20available%20on%20the%20web%20or%20it%20comes%20in%20some%20bespoke%20format%20that%20needs%20translating%20into%20some%20other%20format%20before%20integration%20is%20possible.%20The%20problem%20isn%27t%20just%20formats,%20we%20also%20have%20problems%20with%20identifiers%20and%20names%20for%20the%20things%20we%20talk%20about%20in%20biology,%20such%20as%20genes,%20gene%20functions,%20diseases,%20anatomical%20parts,%20biomedical%20investigations,%20instruments%20etc..%20Luckily%20there%20is%20a%20whole%20community%20of%20biologists%20and%20computer%20scientist%20working%20to%20develop%20ontologies%20that%20will%20provide%20the%20community%20with%20a%20set%20of%20standard%20terminology%20to%20describe%20the%20data%20published%20on%20the%20web%20-%20many%20of%20you%20will%20already%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20Gene%20Ontology,%20but%20other%20ontologies%20now%20exist%20to%20cover%20many%20sub-domains%20of%20biology.%20The%20KUPKB%20makes%20extensive%20use%20of%20these%20ontologies%20to%20provide%20a%20controlled%20and%20consistent%20annotation%20mechanism%20for%20the%20experimental%20data.%20Adopting%20these%20standards%20not%20only%20offers%20new%20ways%20to%20query%20and%20browse%20the%20data%20but%20it%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20integrate%20other%20datasets%20with%20the%20KUPKB%20data,%20providing%20everybody%20adheres%20to%20the%20same%20set%20of%20standards.%20%20Whilst%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20not%20the%20first%20and%20probably%20not%20the%20last%20specialised%20kidney%20database%20that%20will%20emerge%20on%20the%20Web,%20it%20differs%20from%20previous%20efforts%20because%20of%20the%20way%20we%20represent%20and%20publish%20the%20data.%20All%20of%20the%20data%20is%20published%20in%20a%20single%20format%20called%20RDF.%20We%20have%20RDF%20versions%20of%20many%20biological%20databases%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20such%20as%20Entrez%20Gene,%20Uniprot,%20KEGG,%20HMDB,%20Homologene,%20String,%20Gene%20Ontology%20Annotations%20and%20HMDB.%20Various%20mapping%20work%20has%20been%20done%20to%20connected%20all%20of%20these%20databases%20using%20standard%20identifiers.%20Next,%20the%20experimental%20observations%20such%20as%20a%20gene%20list%20from%20a%20microarray%20experiment%20are%20also%20represented%20in%20RDF,%20and%20using%20the%20appropriate%20identifiers,%20linked%20to%20the%20appropriate%20reference%20databases.%20The%20experimental%20data%20is%20described%20using%20terms%20from%20standard%20ontologies%20that%20cover%20terms%20about%20renal%20cells,%20anatomy,%20animal%20models%20and%20diseases.%20This%20gives%20us%20a%20very%20rich%20connected%20knowledge%20base%20of%20facts%20about%20experimental%20observation%20in%20the%20kidney.%20The%20iKUP%20browser%20only%20exposes%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20the%20rich%20data%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20we%20are%20currently%20working%20on%20more%20tools%20for%20this%20site%20that%20expose%20the%20rich%20data%20in%20the%20KUPKB.%20The%20most%2 %20%20The%20primary%20contact%20for%20the%20KUPKB%20is%20via%20the%20support%20[at]%20kupkb.org%20mailing%20list.%20Alternatively%20you%20can%20contact%20any%20of%20the%20group%20members%20from%20Manchester%20or%20Toulouse%20directly.%20Team%20KUPKB%20%20%20%20Dr%20Julie%20Klein%20%20%20Contact:%20julie(dot)klein(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Queen%20of%20the%20KUPKB%20and%20first%20port%20of%20call%20for%20any%20questions%20relating%20to%20the%20KUPKB.%20She%20will%20gladly%20help%20you%20get%20your%20data%20into%20the%20KUPKB%20in%20return%20for%20tea%20and%20biscuits.%20%20%20Bio:%20Julie%20Klein%20received%20her%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20in%202009%20from%20the%20University%20Paul%20Sabatier,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20This%20thesis%20aimed%20to%20unravel%20the%20role%20of%20the%20kinin%20B1%20receptor%20in%20the%20development%20of%20kidney%20inflammation%20and%20fibrosis%20and%20evaluate%20the%20therapeutic%20potential%20of%20a%20B1R%20antagonist%20on%20the%20progression%20of%20nephropathies.%20Since%202009,%20Julie%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20on%20the%20development%20of%20a%20Kidney%20and%20Urinary%20Pathway%20Knowldge%20Base%20(KUPKB).%20%20%20%20%20%20Simon%20Jupp%20%20%20Contact:%20simon(dot)jupp(at)manchester(dot)ac(dot)uk%20%20%20Role:Programmer,%20architect%20and%20ontologist%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20%20%20Bio:%20Simon%20works%20in%20the%20Bio-Health%20Informatics%20Group%20(BHIG)%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manchester.%20He%20has%20degrees%20in%20both%20Biochemistry%20and%20Computer%20Science%20and%20now%20works%20primarily%20as%20a%20research%20bioinformatician.%20His%20interests%20are%20generally%20related%20to%20information%20management,%20but%20more%20specifically,%20using%20computers%20to%20improve%20the%20way%20we%20capture%20,%20manage%20and%20share%20knowledge%20about%20biology.%20Most%20of%20my%20work%20is%20now%20focused%20on%20the%20use%20of%20ontologies%20to%20capture%20knowledge%20in%20some%20computationally%20useful%20form.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Panagiotis%20(Panos)%20Moulos%20%20%20Contact:%20pmoulos(at)eie(dot)gr%20%20%20Role:New%20team%20member,%20trained%20in%20the%20dark%20arts%20of%20R%20and%20currently%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20KUPKB%20tools...%20%20%20Bio:%20Panagiotis%20Moulos%20holds%20a%20diploma%20in%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Physics%20and%20a%20MSc%20in%20Bioinformatics.%20In%202011,%20he%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Bioinformatics%20from%20the%20National%20Technical%20University%20of%20Athens,%20Greece%20(NTUA)%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20statistical%20algorithms%20and%20software%20development%20for%20the%20computational%20analysis%20and%20meta-analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20(DNA%20microarrays,%20Next%20Generation%20Sequencing).%20He%20is%20also%20interested%20in%20the%20application%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20techniques%20regarding%20the%20computational%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data%20the%20integration%20of%20lower%20level%20data%20representations%20(fundamental%20analysis%20of%20high-throughput%20genomic%20data)%20to%20higher%20level%20representations%20(over%20represented%20GO%20categories,%20mapping%20to%20metabolic%20pathways,%20building%20of%20transcriptional%20networks).%20He%20currently%20works%20as%20a%20post-doc%20in%20the%20RF-Lab%20at%20Inserm,%20U1048,%20Toulouse,%20France.%20%20%20%20%20%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra%20%20%20Contact:%20joost-peter(dot)schanstra(at)inserm(dot)fr%20%20%20Role:%20Crash%20test%20dummy%20for%20the%20KUPKB.%20Plays%20a%20mean%20slap%20bass%20guitar.%20%20%20Bio:%20Dr%20Joost%20Schanstra,%20born%201967%20in%20Meppel,%20The%20Netherlands,%20received%20his%20PhD%20in%20Life%20Sciences%20(1996)%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Groningen,%20The%20Netherlands.%20From%201996%20to%201999%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Inserm%20U388%20in%20Toulouse,%20France.%20In%201999%20he%20obtained%20a%20staff%20research%20position%20in%20the%20same%20labor
